\begin{align*}
c_n &amp;= \frac{1}{ T }\int_{ T } f(t)e^{-i n \omega t}dt \\
&amp;= \frac {1} {2} \int_{-1}^{1} \alpha e^t e^{-i n \omega t} dt\\
&amp;= \frac {\alpha} {2 (1 - i n \omega)} (e^{1 - i n \omega} - e^{i n \omega - 1}) \\
&amp;= \frac {\alpha} {2 (1 - i n \pi )} (e^{1 - i n \pi} - e^{i n \pi - 1}) \\
&amp;= \frac {\alpha} {1 - i n \pi} \sinh(1-in\pi) \\
&amp;= \frac {\alpha} {1 - i n \pi} (-1)^n \sinh(1)
\end{align*}

$$
\begin{align*}
c_n &= \frac{1}{ T }\int_{ T } f(t)e^{-i n \omega t}dt \\
&= \frac {1} {2} \int_{-1}^{1} \alpha e^t e^{-i n \omega t} dt\\
&= \frac {\alpha} {2 (1 - i n \omega)} (e^{1 - i n \omega} - e^{i n \omega - 1}) \\
&= \frac {\alpha} {2 (1 - i n \pi )} (e^{1 - i n \pi} - e^{i n \pi - 1}) \\
&= \frac {\alpha} {1 - i n \pi} \sinh(1-in\pi) \\
&= \frac {\alpha} {1 - i n \pi} (-1)^n \sinh(1)
\end{align*}
$$
